ero-tolerance%20policy%E2%80%99%20against%20crime%20by%20the%20Adityanath%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20a%20question%20that%20lingered%20has%20been%2C%20how%20did%20the%20government%20before%20him%20%E2%80%93%20run%20by%20the%20Samajwadi%20Party%20under%20chief%20minister%20Akhilesh%20Yadav%20%E2%80%93%20fare%20in%20terms%20of%20numbers%20when%20it%20came%20to%20alleged%20%E2%80%98encounters%E2%80%99%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20data%20published%20in%20the%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20assembly%20on%20August%208%20shows%20that%20in%20Adityanath%E2%80%99s%20first%20five%20years%20in%20power%2C%20from%202017%20to%202022%2C%20four%20times%20more%20people%20were%20killed%20in%20%E2%80%9Cpolice%20action%E2%80%9D%20than%20during%20Yadav%E2%80%99s%20chief%20ministership%20from%202012%20to%202017.%20Both%20were%20full%20majority%20governments%20with%20chief%20ministers%20directly%20in%20control%20of%20law%20and%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20period%202017-18%20to%202021-2022%2C%20162%20persons%20were%20killed%20in%20%E2%80%9Cpolice%20action%E2%80%9D%2C%20while%2041%20persons%20were%20killed%20from%202012%20to%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20details%2C%20seen%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20were%20published%20in%20the%20form%20of%20a%20written%20reply%20in%20the%20UP%20assembly%20by%20Adityanath%2C%20in%20response%20to%20a%20query%20by%20a%20Samajwadi%20Party%20MLA.%20Adityanath%20is%20directly%20responsible%20for%20law%20and%20order%20in%20the%20state%2C%20by%20virtue%20of%20him%20holding%20the%20Home%20Department%20portfolio.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%202017%20to%202022%2C%20police%20shot%203%2C574%20persons%20or%20suspected%20criminals.%20There%20was%2C%20however%2C%20no%20data%20provided%20for%20the%20number%20of%20suspected%20criminals%20shot%20during%20Yadav%E2%80%99s%20tenure%20or%20the%20year-wise%20break%20up%20of%20the%20persons%20killed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdityanath%E2%80%99s%20first%20tenure%20also%20stands%20out%20in%20comparison%20to%20Yadav%E2%80%99s%20regime%20in%20terms%20of%20attacks%20on%20police%20personnel.%20In%202012-2017%2C%20there%20were%204%2C361%20incidents%20of%20attacks%20on%20police%20personnel.%20However%2C%20from%202017%20to%202022%2C%20the%20number%20of%20attacks%20on%20police%20substantially%20went%20up%2C%20to%205%2C972.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20opposition%20leader%2C%20Yadav%20has%20regularly%20spoken%20out%20against%20the%20spurt%20in%20such%20shootings%20and%20accused%20the%20BJP%20government%20of%20carrying%20out%20%E2%80%98fake%20encounters%E2%80%99%20for%20electoral%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdityanath%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20has%20endorsed%20and%20promoted%20the%20policy%20of%20encounters%2C%20giving%20the%20men%20in%20uniform%20a%20free%20hand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUP%20Police%20have%20maintained%20that%20they%20shoot%20criminals%20only%20in%20self-defence%20and%20that%20they%20prefer%20to%20arrest%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20police%20do%20not%20go%20looking%20for%20violence%2C%20nor%20use%20any%20force%20more%20than%20necessary%2C%20but%20in%20some%20cases%20due%20the%20actions%20of%20the%20criminal%20being%20apprehended%20situation%20arises%20in%20a%20sudden%20and%20inevitable%20manner%20in%20which%20the%20police%20personnel%20are%20constrained%20to%20use%20lawful%20and%20proportionate%20force%20in%20self%20defence%20in%20carrying%20out%20the%20duty%20assigned%20to%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20UP%20government%20had%20told%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20an%20affidavit%20in%20response%20to%20a%20PIL%20filed%20by%20the%20People%E2%80%99s%20Union%20for%20Civil%20Liberties%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20PUCL%20demanded%20a%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20probe%20into%20the%20cases%20of%20alleged%20fake%20encounter%20killings%20or%20an%20SIT%20investigation%20by%20police%20officers%20who%20had%20not%20served%20in%20UP.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691562985000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%