rame%20containing%20a%20lock%20of%20hair%20attributed%20to%20Beethoven%20was%20cut%20from%20his%20head%20by%20Anton%20Felix%20Schindler%20on%20March%2024%2C%201827%2C%20and%20given%20to%20Ignaz%20Moscheles%20after%20Beethoven's%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20unable%20to%20find%20a%20definitive%20cause%20for%20Beethoven's%20deafness%20or%20gastrointestinal%20problems%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Krause%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20we%20did%20discover%20a%20number%20of%20significant%20genetic%20risk%20factors%20for%20liver%20disease.%20We%20also%20found%20evidence%20of%20an%20infection%20with%20the%20hepatitis%20B%20virus%20in%20the%20months%20before%20the%20composer's%20final%20illness.%20Those%20likely%20contributed%20to%20his%20death.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20study%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20Current%20Biology%2C%20%26quot%3BAs%20commonly%20happens%20when%20people%20analyze%20DNA%2C%20the%20researchers%20uncovered%20another%20surprise.%20Beethoven's%20Y%20chromosome%20doesn't%20match%20that%20of%20any%20of%20five%20modern-day%20relatives%20carrying%20the%20same%20last%20name%20and%20sharing%2C%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20genealogical%20records%2C%20a%20common%20ancestor%20with%20Beethoven's%20paternal%20line.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20finding%20points%20to%20an%20extramarital%20%26quot%3Bevent%26quot%3B%20somewhere%20over%20the%20generations%20on%20Beethoven's%20father's%20side%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20the%20authors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20finding%20suggests%20an%20extrapair%20paternity%20event%20in%20his%20paternal%20line%20between%20the%20conception%20of%20Hendrik%20van%20Beethoven%20in%20Kampenhout%2C%20Belgium%2C%20in%20c.%201572%20and%20the%20conception%20of%20Ludwig%20van%20Beethoven%20seven%20generations%20later%2C%20in%201770%2C%20in%20Bonn%2C%20Germany%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Tristan%20Begg%2C%20now%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Cambridge%2C%20UK.