2Funnamed-247x300.jpg%20247w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-649461%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22354%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20does%20seem%20that%2C%20in%20some%20democracies%2C%20the%20courtroom%20is%20taking%20the%20place%20of%20the%20hustings.%20That%E2%80%99s%20most%20evident%20with%20the%20imprisonment%20of%20Imran%20Khan%2C%20widely%20seen%20as%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20most%20popular%20politician.%20He%E2%80%99s%20been%20convicted%20of%20selling%20gifts%20received%20when%20he%20was%20in%20office%20and%20failing%20to%20declare%20the%20proceeds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKhan%E2%80%99s%20three-year%20jail%20sentence%20will%20disqualify%20him%20from%20contesting%20elections%20due%20later%20in%20the%20year.%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20all-powerful%20army%20has%20ensured%20that%20their%20ally-turned-critic%20won%E2%80%99t%20make%20a%20return%20to%20power%20in%20those%20elections.%20And%20just%20to%20make%20doubly%20sure%2C%20they%20have%20disembowelled%20Imran%20Khan%E2%80%99s%20party%2C%20encouraging%20PTI%20leaders%20to%20abandon%20Khan%2C%20and%20hobbled%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20news%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20battery%20of%20court%20cases%20facing%20Donald%20Trump%20%E2%80%93%20he%E2%80%99s%20been%20indicted%20in%20three%20criminal%20cases%2C%20with%20a%20fourth%20said%20to%20be%20imminent%20%E2%80%93%20are%20altogether%20more%20complex%20and%20serious.%20He%20appeared%20in%20court%20in%20New%20York%20last%20week%20and%20declared%20that%20he%20was%20not%20guilty%20of%20the%20most%20grievous%20of%20the%20charges%20he%20faces%2C%20that%20he%20allegedly%20conspired%20to%20overturn%20the%20outcome%20of%20the%202020%20presidential%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20you%20would%20expect%20from%20this%20political%20street%20fighter%2C%20Trump%20is%20complaining%20loudly%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20all%20a%20political%20set-up%20to%20weaken%20his%20bid%20to%20return%20to%20the%20White%20House%20and%20that%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20way%20he%20will%20get%20a%20fair%20trial.%20It%E2%80%99s%20certainly%20the%20case%20that%20Trump%20is%20far-and-away%20the%20frontrunner%20to%20win%20the%20Republican%20nomination%20and%20so%20stand%20against%20Joe%20Biden%20in%20the%20November%202024%20presidential%20election.%20And%20among%20his%20support%20base%2C%20the%20flurry%20of%20litigation%20has%20strengthened%20his%20standing.%20Even%20his%20rivals%20for%20the%20Republican%20nomination%20have%20suggested%20that%20the%20court%20cases%20have%20a%20political%20motive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDonald%20Trump%20is%20the%20biter%20bit.%20In%20his%20first%20presidential%20contest%2C%20he%20repeatedly%20disparaged%20his%20opponent%20as%20%E2%80%98Crooked%20Hillary%E2%80%99%20and%20encouraged%20his%20followers%20to%20chant%3A%20Lock%20Her%20Up!%20Hillary%20Clinton%E2%80%99s%20supposed%20offence%20was%20to%20use%20a%20private%20email%20server%20for%20official%20communications%20when%20serving%20as%20secretary%20of%20state.%20The%20Federal%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20(FBI)%20head%20ruled%20that%20Clinton%20had%20been%20%E2%80%98extremely%20careless%E2%80%99%20but%20advised%20against%20prosecution%20because%20there%20had%20been%20no%20criminal%20intent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20late%2C%20Trump%20has%20redirected%20his%20venom%20towards%20Joe%20Biden%2C%20whom%20he%20has%20described%20%E2%80%93%20without%20offering%20any%20evidence%20%E2%80%93%20as%20the%20most%20corrupt%20ever.%20He%20has%20also%20made%20frequent%20reference%20to%20the%20Biden%20%E2%80%98crime%20family%E2%80%99%2C%20seeking%20to%20tie%20the%20president%20into%20the%20controversy%20about%20the%20conduct%20of%20his%20at%20times%20wayward%20son%2C%20Hunter%20Biden.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20part%20of%20a%20populist%20pattern%2C%20in%20which%20rivals%20are%20not%20simply%20challenged%20on%20their%20policies%2C%20competence%20and%20political%20experience%20but%20denounced%20in%20hyperbolic%20fashion%20as%20corrupt%20and%20criminal.%20It%20coarsens%20politics%20and%20deadens%20normal%20democratic%20debate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%20insists%20that%20it%20has%20had%20no%20role%20at%20all%20in%20instigating%20the%20prosecution%20of%20Donald%20Trump%20and%20that%20all%20decisions%20have%20been%20taken%20free%20of%20any%20political%20pressure.%20Perhaps%20that%E2%80%99s%20so.%20And%20no%20one%20wants%20top%20politicians%20to%20be%20immune%20from%20prosecution.%20But%20the%20perception%20of%20many%20in%20America%20will%20be%20that%20this%20slew%20of%20legal%20action%20against%20a%20former%20president%2C%20with%20the%20cases%20likely%20to%20be%20rumbling%20on%20through%20the%20presidential%20election%20campaign%2C%20is%20designed%20to%20ease%20Joe%20Biden%E2%80%99s%20re-election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20United%20States%2C%20Democrats%20have%20done%20their%20fair%20amount%20of%20demonising%20and%20mud-slinging.%20Their%20initial%20attempt%20to%20impeach%20President%20Trump%20in%202019%2C%20alleging%20that%20he%20had%20solicited%20foreign%20interference%20in%20the%20presidential%20election%2C%20was%20particularly%20unfortunate.%20It%20was%20never%20likely%20to%20lead%20to%20conviction%20and%20gave%20the%20impression%20that%20the%20losing%20party%20was%20behaving%20ungracefully%20in%20defeat.%20And%20this%20took%20some%20of%20the%20moral%20high%20ground%20away%20from%20the%20second%20%E2%80%93%20and%20much%20more%20substantial%20%E2%80%93%20move%20to%20impeach%20Trump%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20storming%20of%20the%20Capitol%20building%20alleging%20incitement%20to%20insurrection.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.economist.com%2Funited-states%2F2023%2F08%2F02%2Fonly-politics-not-the-law-can-stop-donald-trump%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEconomist%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20argued%2C%20only%20politics%2C%20not%20the%20law%2C%20can%20stop%20Donald%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20return%20to%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERahul%20Gandhi%2C%20with%20his%20disqualification%20from%20Parliament%20lifted%2C%20is%20in%20a%20better%20place%20than%20his%20two%20fellow%20defendants.%20Whatever%20the%20merits%20of%20the%20case%20against%20him%2C%20whatever%20the%20wisdom%20of%20the%20words%20he%20uttered%2C%20whatever%20your%20view%20of%20his%20competence%20as%20an%20opposition%20leader%2C%20a%20prominent%20politician%20is%20now%20back%20on%20his%20home%20ground%3A%20Parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20issues%20about%20which%20politics%20revolves%20%E2%80%93%20who%20governs%20and%20to%20whose%20benefit%20%E2%80%93%20are%20best%20resolved%20by%20politics%2C%20not%20prosecution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAndrew%20Whitehead%20is%20an%20honorary%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Nottingham%20in%20the%20UK%20and%20a%20former%20BBC%20India%20Correspondent.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691544634000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F07224922%2FUntitled-design-2023-08-07T224901.751.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Frahul-gandhi-imran-khan-and-trump-is-prosecution-taking-the-place-of-politics%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Under%20populism%2C%20rivals%20are%20not%20simply%20challenged%20on%20their%20policies%2C%20competence%20and%20political%20experience%20but%20denounced%20in%20hyperbolic%20fashion%20as%20corrupt%20and%20criminal.%20It%20coarsens%20politics%20and%20deadens%20normal%20democratic%20debate.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Frahul-gandhi-imran-khan-and-trump-is-prosecution-taking-the-place-of-politics%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Indian%20Armed%20Forces%E2%80%99%20Named%20in%20Complaint%20to%20International%20Criminal%20Court%20on%20Abduction%20of%20Dubai%20Princess%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F09%2F05183155%2FLatifa.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELondon%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20A%20%E2%80%98crime%20report%E2%80%99%20attached%20as%20a%20supporting%20document%20in%20a%20complaint%20lodged%20with%20the%20International%20Criminal%20Court%20(ICC)%20at%20The%20Hague%20in%20the%20Netherlands%20names%20Indian%20%E2%80%9Carmed%20forces%E2%80%9D%20for%20being%20involved%20in%20a%20%E2%80%9Chostile%20boarding%20of%20a%20US%20flagged%20yacht%20in%20international%20waters%2C%20armed%20assault%20and%20grievous%20bodily%20harm%2C%20conspiracy%20to%20commit%20murder%2C%20threatening%20life%2C%20kidnapping%20and%20unlawful%20detention%2C%20trespass%2C%20theft%20and%20unlawful%20damage%20to%20property%20and%20human%20rights%20violations%20and%20torture%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20charge%20refers%20to%20the%20March%202018%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fdubai-princess-sheikh-latifa-pegasus-list%5C%22%3Eabduction%20of%20Princess%20Latifa%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20daughter%20of%20the%20ruler%20of%20Dubai%20and%20prime%20minister%20of%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%20Sheikh%20Mohammad%20bin%20Rashid%20al%20Maktoum%2C%20in%20the%20Arabian%20Sea.%20The%20princess%20had%20run%20away%20from%20her%20father%20and%20her%20family%20in%20Dubai%20and%20was%20heading%20for%20India%20to%20seek%20asylum.%20The%20Sheikh%20is%20himself%20named%20as%20an%20accused.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20complaint%20to%20the%20ICC%20was%20filed%20by%20Jonathan%20Levy%2C%20a%20lawyer%20and%20solicitor%20who%20practices%20both%20in%20Britain%20and%20the%20US%20on%20behalf%20of%20Herve%20Jaubert%2C%20a%20former%20French%20naval%20intelligence%20officer%20who%20captained%20Latifa%E2%80%99s%20yacht.%20He%20charges%20Sheikh%20Mohammad%20of%20%E2%80%98Crimes%20Against%20Humanity%20in%20the%20Matter%20of%20the%20Nostromo%20Incident%20and%20%E2%80%9CPrincess%E2%80%9D%20Sheikha%20Latifa%20Al%20Maktoum%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENether%20India%20or%20the%20UAE%20are%20state%20parties%20to%20the%20Rome%20Statute%20of%20the%20ICC%20but%20France%20%E2%80%93%20the%20country%20Jaubert%20is%20a%20citizen%20of%20%E2%80%93%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20crime%20report%20based%20on%20witness%20statements%20says%3A%20%E2%80%98On%20the%20evening%20of%20the%204th%20of%20March%202018%20and%20without%20warning%2C%20UAE%20and%20Indian%20forces%20unlawfully%20boarded%20%3Cem%3ENostromo%3C%2Fem%3E%20(name%20of%20the%20yacht).%20As%20it%20was%20anchored%20in%20international%20waters.%20The%20military%20raid%20began%20with%20fully%20armed%20forces%20with%20face%20covers%20launching%20stun%20grenades%20and%20waving%20military%20assault%20weapons.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20claims%3A%20%E2%80%98Shamsudheen%20Mohidheen%2C%20the%20(Dubai)%20palace%20manager%2C%20lobbied%20the%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister%20(Narendra%20Modi)%20to%20help.%E2%80%99%20Mohidheen%2C%20who%20is%20said%20to%20be%20Indian%2C%20is%20also%20an%20accused%20in%20the%20complaint.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20complaint%20corroborates%20the%20%E2%80%98Opinion%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20United%20Nations%20Human%20Rights%20Commission%20Working%20Group%20on%20Arbitrary%20Detention%20(WGAD)%20issued%20in%20March%202021.%20This%20said%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20detainee%20(Latifa)%20was%20extradited%20(to%20the%20UAE)%20by%20the%20Indian%20forces%2C%20which%20had%20intercepted%20her%20yacht%20in%20international%20waters%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20Goa%20in%20March%202018%2C%20after%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20of%20India%20had%20made%20a%20personal%20telephone%20call%20to%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20of%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%20and%20the%20ruler%20of%20the%20Emirate%20of%20Dubai%20(Sheikh%20Mohammed).%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20Modi%2C%20according%20to%20WGAD%2C%20was%20the%20one%20to%20ring%20Mohammed%20%E2%80%93%20and%20not%20the%20other%20way%20around%20%E2%80%93%20the%20question%20arises%3A%20what%20due%20diligence%20did%20he%20do%20to%20order%20Indian%20armed%20forces%20to%20forcibly%20return%20Latifa%20to%20Dubai%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20London%20high%20court%20ruled%20in%20December%202019%20that%20Latifa%20was%20thwarted%20in%20her%20attempt%20to%20leave%20the%20UAE%20by%20Indian%20armed%20forces%20in%20international%20waters%20in%20the%20Arabian%20Sea.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.judiciary.uk%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F03%2FAl-M-Factfinding-APPROVED-Judgment-111219-for-publication.pdf%5C%22%3Ejudgment%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20description%20of%20the%20way%20in%20which%20Latifa%20was%20treated%20by%20the%20Indian%20security%20services%20and%20also%2C%20once%20the%20Arabic%20man%20(her%20father%E2%80%99s%20agent)%20had%20identified%20her%2C%20does%20not%20give%20any%20indication%20that%20this%20was%20a%20%E2%80%98rescue%E2%80%99%20rather%20a%20%E2%80%98capture%E2%80%99.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20lieu%20of%20the%20favour%20extended%20by%20Modi%2C%20Dubai%20allegedly%20renditioned%20British%20national%20Christian%20Michel%20to%20Delhi%2C%20where%20he%20has%20been%20imprisoned%20for%20four%20years%20and%20nine%20months%20without%20a%20trial.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fchistian-michel-boris-johnson-letter-modi-princess-latifa%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20Michel%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20(CBI)%20in%20India%20has%20repeatedly%20pressured%20him%20to%20sign%20a%20confession%20to%20say%20he%20bribed%20Sonia%20Gandhi%20in%20the%202010%20AgustaWestland%20VVIP%20helicopter%20deal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20after%2011%20years%20of%20investigation%2C%20the%20CBI%20has%20failed%20to%20unearth%20evidence%20to%20take%20him%20to%20trial.%20%E2%80%9CI%20am%20a%20political%20prisoner%20of%20Mr%20Modi%2C%E2%80%9D%20Michel%20lamented%20in%20a%20letter%20last%20month%20to%20British%20Prime%20Minister%20Rishi%20Sunak.%20%E2%80%9CPrime%20Minister%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9Cyou%20will%20be%20in%20India%20in%20September%3B%20I%20hope%20this%20will%20give%20you%20time%20to%20think%20on%20my%20despatch.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F12%2F21135610%2Fjames-christian-michel-produced-in-court_712f5858-04f6-11e9-87e0-d6de39a6b3f8.jpg%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-323307%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20the%20complaint%20says%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%C2%A0%20complaint%20to%20the%20ICC%2C%C2%A0%20Levy%2C%C2%A0%20on%20behalf%20of%20Herve%20Jaubert%2C%20demands%3A%20%E2%80%9CUnder%20the%20provisions%20of%20Article%2075%20of%20the%20Rome%20Statute%2C%20the%20applicant%20also%20seeks%20reparations%20from%20the%20accused%20to%20compensate%20the%20victims%20for%20their%20damages.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20accused%20is%20the%20current%20president%20of%20Interpol%2C%20Major%20General%20Ahmed%20Naser%20Al-Raisi%2C%20previously%20of%20the%20UAE%E2%80%99s%20Ministry%20of%20Interior.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20accuses%20Al-Raisi%20%E2%80%9Cof%20carrying%20out%20the%20orders%20of%20Sheikh%20Mohammad%20to%20intercept%20a%20US%20flagged%20yacht%20%3Cem%3ENostromo%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20retrieve%20Princess%20Latifa%2C%20and%20neutralise%20the%20crew%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ICC%20was%20asked%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20complaint.%20A%20spokesman%20replied%20that%20it%20does%20not%20comment%20on%20%E2%80%98communications%E2%80%99%20(which%20is%20the%20ICC%E2%80%99s%20official%20term%20for%20complaints%20or%20referrals).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJaubert%20testified%20that%20after%20grabbing%20Latifa%20from%20the%20yacht%2C%20Indian%20armed%20forces%20took%20her%20on%20a%20helicopter%20to%20Mumbai%2C%20from%20where%20she%20was%20flown%20on%20a%20private%20jet%20to%20Dubai.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CShoot%20me%20here!%20Don%E2%80%99t%20take%20me%20back%20(to%20Dubai)!%E2%80%9D%20Latifa%20is%20said%20to%20have%20screamed%20when%20the%20Indian%20forces%20stormed%20the%20yacht%20in%20the%20darkness%20of%20night.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20that%20Latifa%20contacted%20Radha%20Stirling%2C%20CEO%20of%20Due%20Process%20International.%20There%20followed%20a%20WhatsApp%20exchange%20between%20them%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ELatifa%3A%20%E2%80%98Please%20Help.%20Please%20please%20there%E2%80%99s%20men%20outside%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20what%E2%80%99s%20happening.%E2%80%99%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EStirling%3A%20%E2%80%98Record%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EStirling%3A%20%E2%80%98Record%20what%20you%20can%20and%20send%E2%80%9D%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EStirling%3A%20%E2%80%98Are%20you%20on%20a%20boat%3F%20Did%20you%20go%20to%20land%3F%E2%80%99%E2%80%99%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EStirling%3A%20%E2%80%98Are%20guns%20still%20firing%3F%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStirling%20commented%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20involvement%20of%20Al-Raisi%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3ENostromo%3C%2Fem%3E%20incident%20raises%20serious%20concerns%20about%20the%20neutrality%20and%20credibility%20of%20Interpol%20itself.%E2%80%9D%20She%20added%2C%20the%20grave%20crimes%20in%20which%20Al-Raisi%20%E2%80%9Cis%20complicit%2C%20undermine%20public%20trust%20in%20its%20integrity%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStirling%20was%20asked%20how%20the%20complainant%20(Jaubert)%20hoped%20to%20pursue%20his%20wrongdoing%20charges%20against%20the%20accused%20since%20neither%20the%20UAE%20nor%20India%20is%20a%20member%20state%20of%20the%20ICC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20answered%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20complaint%20is%E2%80%A6%20from%20a%20French%20citizen%20respecting%20a%20US%20flagged%20yacht%20in%20international%20waters%E2%80%A6%20enforcement%20of%20any%20order%20against%20them%20is%20the%20responsibility%20of%20the%20ICC%20and%20assets%20belonging%20to%20the%20accused%20are%20held%20in%20ICC%20jurisdiction%20(in%20other%20words%20in%20member%20states).%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20added%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20also%20asked%20for%20an%20oversight%20committee%20investigation.%20The%20Independent%20Oversight%20Mechanism%20(IOM)%20of%20the%20ICC%20is%20authorised%20under%20the%20Rome%20Statute%20(which%20initiated%20and%20governs%20the%20ICC)%20Article%20112(4)%20for%20inspection%2C%20evaluation%20and%20investigation%20of%20the%20court%2C%20in%20order%20to%20enhance%20its%20efficiency%20and%20economy.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20complaint%20appears%20to%20be%20at%20a%20stage%20of%20%E2%80%98preliminary%20examination%E2%80%99.%20This%20means%20the%20office%20of%20the%20prosecutor%20at%20the%20ICC%20must%20first%20determine%20whether%20there%20is%20sufficient%20evidence%20of%20crimes%20of%20sufficient%20gravity%20falling%20within%20the%20ICC%E2%80%99s%20jurisdiction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterpol%20was%20emailed%20twice%20for%20a%20comment%20on%20the%20accusation%20against%20its%20president%20Al-Raisi.%20It%20did%20not%20respond.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fashis-ray%5C%22%3EAshis%20Ray%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20former%20editor-at-large%20of%20CNN.%20He%20currently%20analyses%20international%20affairs%20on%20the%20BBC.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691544606000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F09%2F05183155%2FLatifa.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Findian-armed-forces-complaint-international-criminal-court-dubai-princess%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20complaint%20appears%20to%20be%20at%20a%20stage%20of%20'preliminary%20examination'.%20This%20means%20the%20office%20of%20the%20prosecutor%20at%20the%20ICC%20must%20first%20determine%20whether%20there%20is%20sufficient%20evidence%20of%20crimes%20of%20sufficient%20gravity%20falling%20within%20the%20ICC's%20jurisdiction.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonica